long_desc.thetext:
benchtests/scripts/compare_bench.py, benchtests/scripts/import_bench.py, benchtests/scripts/validate_benchout.py use /usr/bin/python.  They are compatible with both Python 2 and Python 3, so /usr/bin/python is not inappropriate, but the Fedora preference is to make the choice explicit.

This should go into both rawhide and Fedora 28.

long_desc.thetext:
Per

https://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/systemd-devel/2018-May/040746.html
https://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/systemd-devel/2018-May/040757.html

we shouldn't run “telinit u” from glibc_post_upgrade.*.

Also related: https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/glibc/pull-request/6

notes:
This updates contains various updates from the upstream glibc 2.27 release branch, including minor fixes for the `realpath` function and the i386 `memmove` implementation. Python helper scripts in the `glibc-benchtests` subpackage now use `/usr/bin/python3` as the script interpreter (RHBZ#1577223).

Starting with this update, glibc will no longer re-exec systemd during glibc updates (RHBZ#1579225).
